; Negate multiplicity fixture (checkpoint (d), analysis sec 4.5 R9, Q5).
;
; The negate keys on A only, but several distinct pred rows (A, B1), (A, B2)
; ... share that key. Gaining the negated key seen(A) must retract EVERY
; matching pred row (several `-` crossover folds must land, one per pred
; ROW), and losing it must re-derive them all. The pred's extra column B is
; carried DOWNSTREAM (out(A,B) : mid(A,B)) so the multiplicity is observable:
; a wrong per-KEY (rather than per-ROW) crossover would drop the wrong count.
;
; mid(A, B) : feed(A, B), !seen(A).
; out(A, B) : mid(A, B).
; seen(A)   : block(A).                (differential, so both arms live)
#message feed(u64 A, u64 B).
#message block(u64 A) @differential.

#local mid(u64 A, u64 B).
#local seen(u64 A).

#query out(free u64 A, free u64 B).

seen(A) : block(A).
mid(A, B) : feed(A, B), !seen(A).
out(A, B) : mid(A, B).
